examples.en: He owes a great deal to his publishers.
He accused the diary's publishers of blatant opportunism.
Publishers reduced print runs to cut down the cost of warehousing.
He told me he had bought them when they were remaindered by publishers.
Several publishers were asleep at the switch, and missed the book's potential.
Few publishers go to the trouble of giving the number of copies for an edition.
His work was preferred from the cellar of the publishers to the author's garret.
Publishers now have to produce textbooks that pass muster with a slew of faultfinding committees.
